Well, if that's the case, then you don't have to celebrate. There's nothing wrong with not celebrating a national holiday. Just do what makes you feel happy, and ignore anyone who tells you there is something wrong with not celebrating Christmas.
Honestly, I understand. People can be dumb, they can be assholes. Holidays don't feel like holidays anymore. They just kinda feel like regular days. Perhaps you can celebrate by yourself?

Honestly, yeah, people can be narcissistic dickheads who care about others only when it affects them. Especially adults, since they believe they went through a lot, and pride themselves for it, whilst berating anyone who disagrees with them. Thats why they should be ignored if they say that, because they most likely do not care.

I know you may think its a bad idea, but making amends with them might make them want to come back to you. Sure, it won't fix everything, but you at least will be able to see them again. So please, don't do it, you may have made a mistake but you can fix it. I know you can

Your parents would still be broken if you did that, even if they didn't know of your intentions. Same with anyone else who knows you. You may not know it, but I am sure they care for you a lot. So please don't do this. I may not know you, but I can tell you are a great person who deserves happiness
Share with us your story, and all of us here will console you. Please, i may not know you, but i know you do not deserve to die.
I used to be an adventurer like you...
Happy birthday! I may not know you, but I know that its not worth it. There are people who love you and care for you, even if you may not think it. Life is worth living.
